Muffin Tin Doughnuts
  --Cook's Country

Doughnuts:
2 ¾	c (13 3/4 oz) all-purpose flour
1	c (7 oz) sugar
¼	c cornstarch
1	tbsp baking powder
1	tsp salt
½	tsp ground nutmeg
1	c buttermilk
8	tbsp unsalted butter, melted
2	large eggs + 1 large yolk

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 400F. Spray 12-cup muffin tin with vegetable oil spray. Whisk flour, sugar, cornstarch, baking powder, salt, and nutmeg together in bowl. Whisk buttermilk, melted butter, and eggs and yolk together in separate bowl. Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and stir with rubber spatula until just combined. Scoop batter into prepared tin. Bake until doughnuts are lightly browned and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 19-22 min. Let doughnuts cool in tin for 5 min.

Coating:
1	c sugar
2	tsp ground cinnamon
8	tbsp unsalted butter, melted

Whisk sugar and cinnamon together in bowl. Remove doughnuts from tin. Working with 1 doughnut at a time, brush all over with melted butter, then roll in cinnamon sugar, pressing lightly to adhere. Transfer to wire rack and let cool for 15 min. Serve.
